<p>Pay special attention to <a href="https://www.arduino.cc/reference/en/language/functions/communication/serial/parseint/">parseInt()</a> and <a href="https://www.arduino.cc/reference/en/language/functions/communication/stream/streamparsefloat/">parseFloat()</a> commands.</p>

<p>There are two important functions related to the serial input in the code, and that is <a href="https://www.arduino.cc/reference/en/language/functions/communication/serial/available/">Serial.available()</a> and <a href="https://www.arduino.cc/reference/en/language/functions/communication/serial/read/">Serial.read()</a>.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p><strong>Serial.available()</strong> returns the number of characters (i.e. bytes of data) which have arrived in the serial buffer and that are ready to be read.</p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <p><strong>Serial.read()</strong> returns the first (oldest) character in the buffer and removes that byte of data from the buffer.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>So when all the bytes of data are read and no new serial data has arrived, the buffer is empty and Serial.available() will return 0.</p>

