<h2 id="measuring-voltage-and-current-using-a-multimeter">Measuring Voltage and Current using a Multimeter</h2>
<p>A multimeter or a multitester, also known as a VOM (volt-ohm-milliammeter), is an
electronic measuring instrument that combines several measurement functions in one unit. A
typical multimeter can measure voltage, current, and resistance.</p>

